entry.title: Arsipoda spp., Myoporum insulare
entry.content: There were large numbers of these very small beetles on the Myoporum insulare on Providence Road adjacent to Woodlands Historic Park. (These were planted by the council and do not occur in the Park.) I believe the enlarged hind femur identifies it as a flea beetle, tribe Alticini, which narrows it down to one of 232 species according to AFD

entry.title: Rhinotia spp.
entry.content: There were type types of Rhinotia sp. weevils around this morning. The ones with white markings on their back I think are Rhinotia hemisticta. The plain ones, like this, to my eyes seem to have slightly 'fatter' front legs, although they may also be Rhinotia hemisticta. I don't know if this variablility is within the same species or denotes a different species.

entry.title: Rhinotia spp.
